FactorLabs is a high-performance research framework designed for quantitative developers, students, and data-driven investors. It provides a clean ingestion pipeline, canonical price schema, flexible factor â€œsleeveâ€ architecture, and lightweight backtesting tools â€” all built on modern Python tools like Polars and DuckDB.

The project emphasizes transparency, modularity, and speed, allowing you to build and test quant strategies without the bloat of traditional libraries.

ğŸš€ Features
ğŸ“¥ High-Performance Data Ingestion

Yahoo Finance ingestion (ingest_yf.py)

Clean normalization into canonical OHLCV schema

Polars-based transforms

Write to DuckDB or Parquet

Designed to support multiple vendors (Polygon, Tiingo, Alpaca)

âš™ï¸ Fast Analytical Engine

Columnar execution using Polars

SQL interoperability via DuckDB

Zero heavy external dependencies

Vectorized operations instead of loops

ğŸ§© Modular â€œSleevesâ€ Architecture

A sleeve is a self-contained module that generates signals or factors.

Examples:

Momentum Sleeve (rolling returns, cross-section ranking)

Mean Reversion Sleeve (z-scores, RSI-style behavior)

Stat-Arb Sleeve (pairs, spreads, cointegration)

ML Sleeve (tree-based predictors, alt-data signals)

Sleeves can be added, combined, weighted, or swapped without rewriting the entire system.

ğŸ“Š Lightweight Backtester

Daily or intraday frequency

Position sizing & allocation

PnL tracking, benchmark comparison

Drawdown, volatility, Sharpe, turnover

Simple risk model hooks

