ğŸ“¦ Installation
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/FactorLabs
cd FactorLabs
pip install -r requirements.txt

ğŸ Quick Start
1. Ingest Data
python src/ingest/ingest_yf.py --tickers AAPL MSFT SPY \
                               --start 2018-01-01 \
                               --end 2025-01-01 \
                               --interval 1d

2. Load Processed Data (Python)
from src.core.data_loader import load_prices

df = load_prices("data/processed/prices.parquet")
print(df.head())

3. Run a Simple Sleeve
from src.sleeves.momentum import momentum_signals

signals = momentum_signals(df, window=20)

4. Backtest
from src.backtest.engine import Backtester

bt = Backtester(prices=df, signals=signals)
results = bt.run()
results.plot()

ğŸ”§ Development Philosophy

FactorLabs follows three principles:

1. Simplicity > Abstraction

No thousand-line classes.
No magic methods.
Functions, dataclasses, and small modules.

2. Speed by Design

Polars + DuckDB allow fast analytics even on large universes.

3. Hackable by Anyone

Built for learning, experimentation, and extension.

ğŸ§ª Testing

Tests are located under:

tests/
   test_ingest.py
   test_sleeves.py
   test_backtester.py


Run tests with:

pytest 
